# Cursor AI Rules for all-religious-texts

# Project Context
This repo is the core specification authority for All Religious Texts (ART) by CRINE (www.crine.in).
Schemas live in schemas/, master registries in metadata/, validation in validators/, tools in tools/.

# Key Rules
1. Never place actual corpus datasets in this repository (only examples in examples/).
2. Run `python3 validators/run_all.py` after editing schemas, tooling, or metadata.
3. Follow PEP 8 and Black formatting for Python.
4. Keep JSON 2-space indented with UTF-8 encoding.
5. All directories must be lowercase kebab-case.
